    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-15T04:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-15T04:35:00-05:00" n="369"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1874: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-15T13:00:00+03:25"
                            >May 15, 1942—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 16—8:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>157. Referring to the Department’s No. 116, March 5 [<hi rend="italic">May
                    6</hi>], 10 p.m.<note n="75" xml:id="d369fn75">See footnote 72, <ref
                            target="#pg_322">p. 322</ref>.</note> Minister of War informs me Soviet
                    authorities have given permission for 500 Iranian troops to proceed to Rezaieh
                    area and that they will leave at once. He is endeavoring to obtain permission
                    for additional 1,000 to be sent there.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tabriz.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
